European foulbrood of honey bees, Belgium
-----------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 10 Jun 2014 from Dr Pierre Naassens, [chief veterinary officer, CVO, Directorate of Animal Health and Safety of Animal Products, Federal Agency for the Safety of the Food Chain, Brussels], Belgium

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Jun 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 5 Jun 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: August 2009
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Melissococcus plutonius_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Stambruges, Hainaut
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Jun 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: apiary
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Bees (hives) / 4 / 1 / -- / 1 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Bees (hives) / 25 / ** / ** / **
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; zoning; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); modified stamping out; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Veterinary and Agrochemical Research Centre (CODA - CERVA) (regional reference laboratory) / Bees / pathogenic agent isolation on culture / 5 Jun 2014 / Positive
Veterinary and Agrochemical Research Centre (CODA - CERVA) (regional reference laboratory) / Bees / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 5 Jun 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

